Workday Business Analyst II - On behalf on our client in Higher Education, Procom Services is looking for a Business Analyst II.  Workday Business Analyst II Job Details
The Business Analyst contractor position will report to Stakeholder Engagement Lead, as a member of the Readiness team and will be engaged in multiple types of SURGE support activities, including:
Rapid deployment – analyst resources to address immediate, short-term needs, incoming questions, and troubleshooting (also referred to as “traffic cops” or “runners”);
Processing support - locally or regionally stationed resources to provide direct, hands-on assistance with Workday HCM process initiation, inputs, validations, approvals, and troubleshooting;
Unit documentation and proactive business process mapping to address inefficiencies, bottlenecks, processing inconsistencies, or staffing issues.
Specifically, the Business Analyst contractor will:
Become familiar with the specific Workday configurations and processing by engaging in near-term documentation and testing activities;
Interact directly with management-level stakeholders in Dean and VP offices to understand concerns and respond to questions about specific business processing tasks and impacts;
Assist with process documentation, mapping, knowledge transfer, and communication tasks;
Provide feedback to the Workday program readiness team;
Process Workday HCM transactions on behalf of (or in addition to) departmental personnel, as appropriate.
Workday Business Analyst II Mandatory Skills
2 or more years of experience as an analyst or project manager on a Workday HCM implementation project;
2 or more years of experience in a higher education business environment;
Familiarity with standard Workday HCM/Payroll concepts, practices, and processes;
Knowledge of commonly-used concepts, practices, and procedures within higher education;
Experience working as part of a large systems implementation team, utilizing a variety of coordination and communication strategies, and tracking activities to project plan milestones;
Proven ability to review, analyze, and evaluate system functionality in the context of user processing needs;
Proven ability to troubleshooting business processing issues, identify and mitigate risks, and determine steps required to efficiently resolve problems;
Exceptional verbal and written communication skills;
Experience with business process analysis, mapping, and documentation;
Ability to multi-task and use independent judgement in prioritizing simultaneous tasks.
Workday Business Analyst II  Nice to Have Skills
3 or more years of experience implementing Workday systems in a university environment;
3 or more years of experience working in a business position in a large public research institution;
Experience facilitating operational readiness and triage activities in a large systems implementation project;
Experience with executive-level stakeholder engagement or readiness activities as part of a higher education systems implementation project.
Workday Business Analyst II Start Date/Location
May 2018
Austin, Texas
Workday Business Analyst II Assignment Length10 Months (2/29/19)

The Business Analyst will gather & define business requirements, data validation and analysis, and client delivery related assistance in support of ePASS® priorities and vision. As an Inovalon Business Analyst, you will become a key player in ensuring our continued success as part of a team of diverse individuals who are developing and rolling-out new product offerings to our clients. You will work collaboratively in our fast paced environment on duties, often in a cross-functional capacity that may be inclusive of product development, operations, data analytics, reporting, documentation and execution-related assistance in support of member and provider-directed interventions. From demonstrating ability to work independently and good technical skills, strong analytical and problem solving skills, the Business Analyst will support the product technology, product operations and provide value across, and gain exposure to, the ePASS® product and the multiple Inovalon components it touches.

Responsibilities:

Develop & create business requirements for Agile development teams;
Support business development opportunities in the expansion of product features and services;
Build, test and report on business user acceptance test cases;
Perform complex data analysis, including production of queries, in support of ad-hoc and standing management or customer requests;
Utilize and apply T-SQL and other data analysis tools to develop insights into health care outcomes and the drivers of such outcomes;
Perform analytics on a relational datasets to identify root causes, patterns, trends and recommend solutions;
Assemble data analytical input, including charts, tables, graphs, and other analysis for executive-level presentations and client reporting;
Develop appropriate methodologies for collecting, analyzing and presenting data products;
Develop and refine specifications for core features of quality improvement product to generate key performance indicators;
Support client relationships by actively working with internal product teams and client services to provide client product updates, presentations and demos;
Liaise with the Operations and IT departments to prepare external product release notifications;
Manage external product documentation such as service guides, user guides, and other collateral materials; and
Support product development activities by tracking product backlog and roadmap.

Qualifications:

Bachelor's degree in a technical field such as Engineering, Health Science, or equivalent;
2+ years of business analysis experience with some healthcare data experience preferred;
2+ years of SQL experience & designing and conducting user acceptance testing preferred;
Possess agile software development methodology experience;
Excellent analytical skills and the ability to understand the company's products and process;
Ability to set priorities and work on multiple tasks simultaneously. Work under minimal supervision on complex projects;
Knowledge of MS Excel, Word, Visio, PowerPoint and Team Foundation Server (TFS) is preferred;
Professionally skilled in personal presentation, verbal, and written communication; and
Possess meticulous organizational skills.


Inovalon provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, national origin, or protected veteran status and will not be discriminated against on the basis of disability.PI102001338

As a Business Analyst for Pacific Alaska Wholesale (PAW), you will create and analyze reports and use high-level quantitative skills to provide data-driven recommendations to key stakeholders to drive positive change. If you are a strategic thinker able to identify opportunities for process improvement, and new reporting and analytical tools; then you are the right fit to join our team in Anchorage.


Joining NWCI gives you the opportunity for growth and development throughout the company, a competitive salary and benefits package, and to be part of a dynamic and diverse culture.


NWCI is a leading retailer to under-served rural communities and urban neighborhood markets in the following regions: Northern Canada, Western Canada, rural Alaska, the South Pacific islands, and the Caribbean. Our stores offer a broad range of products and services with an emphasis on food. Our value offer is to be the best local shopping choice for everyday household and local lifestyle needs. Check out northwest.ca for more information.


Your Role:



 Ensure the PAW office and computing production system (ERP) provides reliable, stable, and accessible services for the use of stakeholders and service provider;

Monitor PAW functions, processes, and activities to improve operational and computer-based business applications for the most effective use of capital, equipment and people;

Develop, implement, and provide effective and timely management information to the business stakeholders;

Analyze and develop documentation of current and future business requirements;

Develop performance measures that provide actionable insight into sales growth within the wholesale business; and

Manage physical warehouse inventory and ongoing inventory accuracy;







Desired Skills & Experience:



Bachelor’s degree and 5 years of experience or equivalent combination of education and experience;
Enterprise Resource Planner System management and implementation;
Pick database expertise;
E-commerce exposure;
Possess solid logistics background;
Retail or wholesale food experience a plus;
Exceptional organizational and time management skills;
Experience in managing, training, and developing team members; and
Ability to learn and understand the Enterprise Resource Planner


We thank all applicants for their interest; however only those selected for an interview will be contacted. A competitive salary is being offered along with opportunities to learn, develop and advance throughout the organization.

