Our client is seeking a Business Analyst to perform business analysis, design specifications, testing, maintenance, periodic enhancements and on-going support of base and custom-developed software applications within JD Edwards Enterprise One. This position requires a detailed understanding of the features and functionality of the JD Edwards 9.x applications and their integrations to other modules or applications. This position will interact closely with representatives of various business areas while working closely with other business analysts, developers and others within the IT department to deliver solutions. This position will provide expert-level technical and functional analysis and configuration/designing services in our client's multi-company, multi-national environment. This position should be experienced in trouble-shooting critical and non-critical production issues with the capability to solve problems without supervision or oversight from others.
RESPONSIBILITIES:  

Keep updated of new JDE releases and applications and present opportunities for improvement to the business;
Establish and maintain strong business relationships with both senior and operating level business leaders;
Be a “Thought Business Partner”, i.e. engaged with business owners to ensure business process optimization;
Educate business partners on roles, responsibilities, processes and deliverables required to ensure effective delivery of new technology solutions;
Create and maintain thorough, up-to-date, functional and technical systems documentation for any and all customization and maintenance actions taken;
Influence internal stakeholders to achieve the desired outcomes, including process improvement;
Perform and document functional test conditions and expected results; resolve any issues of functionality;
Extensively collaborate with our client's global initiatives in Accounting and Manufacturing and related areas;
Ensure JD Edwards data integrity and perform data recovery as required;
Monitor system performance and minimize down time by correcting issues, implementing run time improvement, and developing contingency plans
Establish strong relations and partnerships with major applications vendors such as Oracle, IBM, Microsoft and others and work with them in maximizing our client's investment in investing in their business technologies and solutions. Ensure contract compliance by vendors and monitor vendor performance
Promote and support IT policies and procedures within the group;
Establish and maintain close working relationships with internal and external contacts including project managers, staff, suppliers, consultants, and contractors;
Perform other duties as assigned.


 
Experience:  Minimum of 5-7years experience in related field including expertise on the Oracle JDEdwards ERP Enterprise One –Manufacturing and Accounting;
Demonstrated subject matter expert in the JD Edwards financials and the related business processes preferred.
Travel Requirements: Approximately 10% travel
Education:  Bachelors or Master’s degree in business and/or technical field.
